snippet: While Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo heralded the overall numbers as a sign of the program’s success, having three out of four enrollees on Medicaid could impose a heavy burden on public finances.
abstract: Cuomo administration reports that about two million New York State residents have signed up for insurance under the Affordable Care Act; figures indicate that three quarters of applicants qualified for Medicaid, proportion that could weigh heavily on state budget.
lead_paragraph: While Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo heralded the overall numbers as a sign of the program’s success, having three out of four enrollees on Medicaid could impose a heavy burden on public finances.
